et Annie Wyman.";i:19;s:151:"Netflix is giving viewers their first look at Sandra Ohs upcoming comedy The Chair ahead of its August premiere with a sneak peek at the opening scene.";i:20;s:35:"The Chair follows Ohs character Dr.";i:21;s:109:"Ji-Yoon Kim as she navigates her new role as the Chair of the English department at the prestigious academic.";i:22;s:49:"The premiere as of now is dated 20th August 2021.";i:23;s:51:"The comedy-drama series is a curious-filled series.";i:24;s:176:"It remarks the social figures features and emotions of being a woman as happiness to chair the top position in a university and the anxiety to overcome the protests and trials.";i:25;s:61:"And at the same time facing the challenges of being a single.";i:26;s:11:"Sep 5 2014.";i:27;s:303:"The competition element is an intriguing twist but what makes The Chair so compelling beyond the usual monetary and production crises youd expect during a four-week shoot in wintry Pittsburgh on a 600000 budget is watching two distinct personalities shape the material in such thoroughly different ways.";i:28;s:121:"A review of The Chair the new Netflix series starring Sandra Oh Jay Duplass and Holland Taylor co-created by Amanda Peet.";i:29;s:46:"Netflixs satire of contemporary academia is a.";i:30;s:110:"Social justice scandals play out in Netflixs newest hit The Chair echoing college campuses across the country.";i:31;s:39:"The shows empathy is remarkable but as.";i:32;s:261:"TV-Recaps-Reviews Friday February 21 2020 Netflix Orders 6 Episodes of Dramedy The Chair Starring Sandra Oh and Jay Duplass Netflix has today given a series order to the original half-hour dramedy series The Chair starring Sandra Oh Killing Eve and Jay Duplass.";i:33;s:30:"2021 TV-MA 1 Season TV Dramas.";i:34;s:152:"At a major university the first woman of color to become chair tries to meet the dizzying demands and high expectations of a failing English department.";i:35;s:37:"Sandra Oh Jay Duplass Holland Taylor.";i:36;s:90:"A